FBIS3-25310 "drafr031_c_94019" FBIS-AFR-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA APLA Commander Sabelo Phama Killed in Car Accident MB1002135494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1100 GMT 10 Feb 94 MB1002135494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The commander of APLA [Azanian People's Liberation Army], Mr. Sabelo Phama, has been killed in a road accident in Tanzania. PAC [Pan-Africanist Congress] officials said in Johannesburg that the vehicle in which Mr. Phama was traveling with a bodyguard had been involved in a collision with a lorry while on his way to the Zimbabwean capital, Harare, from Tanzania. The bodyguard is in a critical condition in a hospital in Tanzania. The officials said Mr. Phama had been on his way to Harare apparently to prepare for his return to South Africa where he was to assume a major role in the PAC's election campaign. He is expected to be buried in Transkei.
